WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'Cellz' is a 2 player strategy game. The goal is to get a
certain number of cells before the opposing player does. The
game is based in part on the cellular reproduction (hence its
name), but it is completely random.

  You can choose the total number of cells to get (between 10
and 150 cells), when you have choosen a number, click on the
'Play!' button to play the game.

  The game is played in an area of 20 by 20 spaces which is
surrounded by a wall. On each turn, the players place a cell
(by clicking at any position inside the game area) and another
cell may appear. If a cell do appear, it will always be
positioned on a space next to the cell placed by the player
(either at left, at right, upward or downward).

  An arrow on top of the game board indicates, by its direction,
which player has the greatest number of cells. If the arrow is
pointing in both directions, it means that the players have the
same number of cells.

  Have fun!

